Vice President Kamala Harris spoke with World Health Organization (WHO) Director-General Dr. Tedros Adhanom Ghebreyesus to discuss the United States' decision to reverse its withdrawal from the WHO. The Vice President emphasized that the Biden administration believes the WHO is crucial in controlling COVID-19 and improving global health and pandemic preparedness. They also discussed the United States' role in the global public health response to the pandemic. Vice President Harris expressed support for efforts to strengthen the global COVID-19 response and mitigate its impacts, particularly on women and girls. The importance of global cooperation in making America safer was also emphasized. The Director-General thanked the Vice President for the call and congratulated her and President Biden on their inauguration. Both parties expressed a desire to meet in person.